# Terminal Commands for PFAI

## Terminal 1 — Backend

1. Open Terminal 1 and change to the project directory:

    cd "d:\4th Sem\Projects\PFAI"

2. Create and activate the virtual environment:

    python -m venv .venv
    .\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1

3. Install dependencies:

    pip install -r requirements.txt

4. Start the backend server:

    uvicorn backend.api.main:app --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8000 --reload


## Terminal 2 — Frontend

1. Open Terminal 2 and change to the project directory:

    cd "d:\4th Sem\Projects\PFAI"

2. Activate the same virtual environment:

    .\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1

3. Start the Streamlit frontend:

    streamlit run frontend/app.py


## Open in browser

- Frontend: http://localhost:8501
- Backend health: http://localhost:8000/health


## Optional: Run tests

In either terminal after activation:

    pytest


## Optional: Docker compose

Build and start the full stack:

    docker compose up --build

Stop the stack:

    docker compose down


## Environment variables

Backend example:

    API_HOST=0.0.0.0
    API_PORT=8000
    MODEL_BUNDLE_PATH=models/trained_multiclass_smoke/best_model.pkl
    SAFEGUARD_DB_PATH=safeguard_ai.db
    BACKEND_LOG_FILE=logs/backend.log
    PREDICTION_CACHE_DIR=models/cache/predictions
    JWT_SECRET_KEY=replace-with-a-long-random-secret
    ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:8501
    USE_JAX_INFERENCE=true

Frontend example:

    SAFEGUARD_API_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8000


## Sample admin creation / login

Create admin:

    curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/auth/create-admin \
      -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
      -d "{\"username\":\"admin_user\",\"password\":\"StrongPass123\"}"

Login:

    curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/auth/login \
      -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
      -d "{\"username\":\"admin_user\",\"password\":\"StrongPass123\"}"
